{
  "stem": "19502.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "For the Russians?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "For-- for me?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was a very good life and a carefree life till the Germans came in.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When-- before [INAUDIBLE] the Germans came in, when-- when the war broke out in June, in 1941, in June, so the-- the-- you know, the-- the Russians started to leave our town, you know.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They-- they moved from-- they-- they backed off and went back to Russia, you see.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So of course they evacuated first their own families, because the Russians came in here, and they settled.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I mean, they were [INAUDIBLE] two years.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So they settled.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So they moved their children, their wives and the children.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They moved out back to Russia, even though the border was still there.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Even though it was Russia, but the border was still-- our town was on the border.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Then--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not yet.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Just before, in 1941, in June.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Just before we were invaded by the German army, the Russian evacuated you know, into the-- you see, because our town was right on the border.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, after 9 or 10 o'clock you couldn't walk the streets-- on the street, because it's-- it was a border.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then it's no man's land.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then again the Novograd-Volynsk.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So what-- what happened, when they-- they moved out first the families, then they said now, look.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Now, people, you can run with us.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The Germans are coming.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Come with us.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So many people did go.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Packed up and put on the wagon-- horse and wagon, you know, horse and buggy, and all their stuff, whatever they needed.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they did go.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And down there, once they come to Zhytomyr, or down to there, the trains, and they took them deeper into Russia.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
